
[1]desperation

   DESPERATION, n.

   1. A despairing; a giving up of hope; as desperation of success.

   2. Hopelessness; despair; as, the men were in a state of desperation.
   Hence,

   3. Fury; rage; disregard of safety or danger; as, the men fought with
   desperation; they were urged to desperation.
